{"status":200,"errors":[],"data":{"_id":"581fd25b54e6080aa866a838","name":"Alexandria","unLoCode":"EGALY","country":{"_id":"581c9a0937c38af7940e06b3","name":"Egypt"},"coordinates":[29.8666,31.1833],"additionalDescription":"          Alexandria Port is Egypt’s principal commercial harbor, handling about 60% of Egypt’s foreign trade. It lies on Egypt’s northern coast between the Mediterranean Sea and Lake Mariout, approximately 220 km northwest of Cairo. The port consists of two main harbors, the Eastern (shallow, unused for large navigation) and the Western harbor (used for commercial trade), and incorporates the Free Zone and adjacent to Dekheila Port, both under APA supervision.​\n\nNatural and Navigational Characteristics\n     *Coordinates: Latitude 31° 11' 36.9'' N / Longitude 29° 52' 34.5'' E​\n     *Entrance Channel Width: 400 m​\n     *Tide Range: 0.46 m above mean level​\n     *Average Water Density: 1.30 g/cm³​\n     *Weather: Northwesterly winds, 2–3 Beaufort in summer, 3–4 in winter​\n     *Rain Season: October to February​\n     *Load Line Zone: Summer​\n     *Max Vessel Size: LOA 213 m, beam 36.5 m, draft 12.8 m (Grain Basin), up to 150,000 DWT.​\n\nOperational Zones and Berths\nThe port is divided into six functional zones:\n     *Zone 1 (Berths 5–15): General cargo\n     *Zone 2 (Berths 16–28): Ro-Ro, passenger terminal, barge, stuffed bulk\n     *Zone 3 (Berths 35–47): General cargo, barge discharge\n     *Zone 4 (Berths 50–68): Containers, cement, coal, fertilizers, general cargo\n     *Zone 5 (Berths 71A–85): Molasses, timber, grains, flour, general cargo\n     *Zone 6 (Berths 86–87): Oil dock area — edible oil, bunkers, livestock berth (Berth 86 connected via 2 km refinery pipeline)\n     *The port does not have oil storage facilities within its premises.​\n\nCargo and Terminals\n     *Grain and Bulk: 9 terminals (60–210 m length // 6–11 m draft)\n     *Conventional/Multi-purpose (MPP): 27 terminals (70–360 m length // 5–11 m draft)\n     *Container Handling: Managed mainly by Alexandria Container & Cargo Handling Company (AlexCont).​\n\nAnnual Traffic and Capacity\n     *Around 5,700 vessels visit annually.\n     *Total cargo handled: 56.6 million tons (dry, liquid, general).\n     *Container throughput: 1.61 million TEU.\n     *Passengers handled: 261,700 annually.​\n\nTransit and Dangerous Cargo\nAccording to the Alexandria Port Authority’s official navigation guidance, transit and shifting of IMO containers onboard are allowed, consistent with existing port safety and environmental regulations managed in coordination with the Egyptian Maritime Safety Authority (EAMS).​\n\nISO and Authority Information\n     *Certification: ISO 9001:2015 Quality Management System accredited.\n     *Managing Body: Alexandria & El Dekheila Port Authority (APA).\n     *Official Website: https://apa.gov.eg/en/\n     *Email Contact: info@apa.gov.eg.​","liftsCranes":{"0-24":{"checked":true,"details":[]},"25-49":{"checked":true,"details":[]},"50-99":{"checked":true,"details":[]},"100-149":{"checked":true,"details":[]},"150+":{"checked":true,"details":[]}},"portLimitations":{"maxDraught":12.8,"maxDWT":150000,"maxBeam":36.5,"meanTide":3,"maxLOA":548},"facilities":{"breakBulk":true,"dryBulk":true,"dryDock":true,"container":true,"liquid":true,"lpg":true,"lng":true,"roro":true,"passenger":true,"multipurpose":true,"bunkering":true,"steel":true,"shipyard":true,"reefer":true},"serviceProviders":[{"_id":"637b5de85fd5e1aacee32768","activities":["Port Agency"],"emails":["ahmed.salama@med-logistic.com"],"name":"Med Logistics & Trading","phones":[{"code":"+20","phone":"1223371974"}],"address":"21 ELSafa St,Smouha","PIC":"Ahmed Salama","limitations":[],"__v":6},{"_id":"63c2aa831f0a102994486b2a","activities":["Port Agency"],"emails":["m.elshazly@tivolishipagent.com"],"name":"Tivoli Ship agent","phones":[{"code":"+20","phone":"1014484883"}],"address":"10 Abo Obida ebn el garah - el Nozha","PIC":"Eng.Mohamed El Shazly","limitations":[],"__v":6},